            <div type="edition" subtype="transcription" ana="b1">
                <p xml:lang="heb">ד<unclear>י</unclear>כר לתב יוסה בר<lb/> תנחנם בר
                        ב<unclear>י</unclear>טה וב<unclear>נוי</unclear><lb/> ד
                        עבדי<unclear>ן</unclear> הדה ט<unclear>ב</unclear>לה<lb/> תהי
                        ל<unclear>הו</unclear>ן ב<unclear>רכ</unclear>ת<unclear>ה</unclear><lb/><gap
                        reason="lost" unit="line" quantity="1"/><lb/> י<unclear>ש</unclear>
                    <gap reason="lost" unit="character" quantity="10"/>
                    <lb/>תדה ט<unclear>ב</unclear><supplied reason="lost" cert="low">לה</supplied>
                    <gap reason="lost" unit="character" quantity="2"/><lb/> ברש<unclear>ת</unclear>
                    <orig><supplied reason="lost">ל</supplied></orig>
                    <gap reason="lost" unit="character" quantity="5"/></p>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" ana="b1">
                <p>In pious remembrance; Yoseh (Joseph) the son of Tanhum, the son of Bitah, and his
                    sons, who have bad this TBLH; which willb e a blessing for them … this TBLH …
                    blessing for (them? forever?)</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary" ana="b1">
                <p>TBLH is likely a loanword - the Latin tabula - which refers to the mosaic itself.
                    Subsequent editions tend to reconstruct the grandfather's name as Butah
                    intead.</p>
            </div>
